WEBVTT

00:04.526 --> 00:04.700
.

00:04.743 --> 00:06.702
male announcer: Previously
on "New Amsterdam"...

00:06.745 --> 00:08.269
- All my patients,

00:08.312 --> 00:09.487
all their despair,
it just becomes a part of me,

00:09.531 --> 00:11.489
and I'm not going
to see patients anymore.

00:11.533 --> 00:12.969
- Dr. Sharpe and I are leaving.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.666
We're leaving New Amsterdam.
We're moving to London.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.494
- I'd like to introduce
you all

00:16.538 --> 00:19.584
to the new medical director
of New Amsterdam.

00:19.628 --> 00:21.021
[dramatic music]

00:21.064 --> 00:23.110
- We go way back,
don't we, Max?

00:23.153 --> 00:24.850
♪

00:24.894 --> 00:26.156
- Listen, Karen.

00:26.200 --> 00:28.158
Yeah, uh, Karen,

00:28.202 --> 00:30.160
would you just stop walking
for one second?

00:30.204 --> 00:31.466
- Why? So you can ask me

00:31.509 --> 00:33.207
to reconsider hiring
Veronica Fuentes?

00:33.250 --> 00:35.165
- No, so I can beg you.
Plead, grovel.

00:35.209 --> 00:37.341
She is the exact wrong person
for the job.

00:37.385 --> 00:38.995
- She's far more qualified
to be medical director

00:39.039 --> 00:40.127
than you are.

00:40.170 --> 00:41.302
- Maybe on paper,
but I trained under her.

00:41.345 --> 00:42.520
- And look how wonderful
you turned out.

00:42.564 --> 00:44.261
- Despite her.
I have seen her in action.

00:44.305 --> 00:46.742
She is ruthless, corporate,
financially motivated.

00:46.785 --> 00:49.310
- Like, like, love.
- She's not one of us.

00:49.353 --> 00:51.268
She completely lacks
the New Amsterdam spirit.

00:51.312 --> 00:52.617
- Unlike you, Max, the board

00:52.661 --> 00:54.402
had to consider
the future of this hospital,

00:54.445 --> 00:57.100
and we were thrilled when
Dr. Fuentes accepted our offer.

00:57.144 --> 00:58.493
She's here to stay.

01:00.364 --> 01:01.626
- Where's my desk?

01:01.670 --> 01:02.758
- Oh, I just thought
the natural light

01:02.801 --> 01:04.107
was better on this side
of the room.

01:04.151 --> 01:05.065
- Oh, you thought
the light was better there?

01:05.108 --> 01:06.066
That's--that's lovely.

01:06.109 --> 01:07.589
I am still the medical director

01:07.632 --> 01:08.938
of this hospital.

01:08.981 --> 01:10.200
My decision stands,

01:10.244 --> 01:11.375
and I happen to like my desk

01:11.419 --> 01:13.160
on the shady side
of the office.

01:13.203 --> 01:14.987
- Max, put on some sunscreen,
and let it go.

01:15.031 --> 01:17.860
I want you to spend the next
five weeks passing the torch.

01:17.903 --> 01:19.166
Bring Dr. Fuentes up to speed.

01:19.209 --> 01:20.558
From this point on,

01:20.602 --> 01:22.299
I want you two
joined firmly at the hip.

01:22.343 --> 01:24.214
- Oh, just like old times,
except back then,

01:24.258 --> 01:26.216
you were a bit more
in the background.

01:26.260 --> 01:27.913
- Yeah, this isn't gonna work.

01:27.957 --> 01:29.263
- Wow, seems like the only one

01:29.306 --> 01:32.004
lacking that New Amsterdam
spirit, Max, is you.

01:32.048 --> 01:33.658
- [scoffs]
- As it turns out,

01:33.702 --> 01:35.225
you'll get the chance
to collaborate

01:35.269 --> 01:37.227
right off the bat,
thanks to this.

01:37.271 --> 01:39.229
A generous donation...
- I got it.

01:39.273 --> 01:40.752
- From Steve and Susan Gerlach,

01:40.796 --> 01:43.451
philanthropists
and longtime hospital donors.

01:43.494 --> 01:45.148
They've gifted New Amsterdam

01:45.192 --> 01:47.063
with attractive land
in East New York worth--

01:47.107 --> 01:48.412
- $10 million.

01:48.456 --> 01:50.806
- That's right.
I want you and Veronica

01:50.849 --> 01:52.634
to decide what to do
with the land.

01:54.026 --> 01:56.246
- What if we can't agree?

01:56.290 --> 01:58.161
- I don't care
if it takes a thumb war.

01:58.205 --> 02:00.903
Figure it out.
- Bye, Karen.

02:00.946 --> 02:02.644
- Thanks, Karen.
- Bye!

02:02.687 --> 02:08.040
♪

02:08.084 --> 02:09.433
- Pardon me, thank you.

02:09.477 --> 02:12.044
Make a hole.
Thank you. Thank you.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.829
Excuse me.

02:13.872 --> 02:15.135
Okay.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.877
Babe, surprise!

02:18.921 --> 02:20.836
I got you a bagel.

02:22.011 --> 02:23.143
Where's Leyla?

02:23.186 --> 02:24.361
- You just missed her.

02:24.405 --> 02:26.407
She went home
about ten minutes ago.

02:26.450 --> 02:28.844
Hey, since she's gone,
can I--can I have that bagel?

02:35.720 --> 02:42.684
♪

02:49.299 --> 02:52.346
[indistinct PA announcement]

02:56.698 --> 02:59.222
- Turkey, egg white omelet,
spanakopita,

02:59.266 --> 03:00.441
and two joes to go.

03:00.484 --> 03:01.964
- Right here.
You can keep the change.

03:02.007 --> 03:03.922
- Does your wife want
honey or agave?

03:03.966 --> 03:07.230
- Oh, actually, the queen
accompanying me isn't my wife.

03:07.274 --> 03:09.798
She is my lover
from a blossoming

03:09.841 --> 03:12.931
and healthy
polyamorous relationship.

03:12.975 --> 03:16.239
- It's fine. It's fine.

03:16.848 --> 03:19.068
Here's your spanakopita,
Dr. Woke-in-stein.

03:19.111 --> 03:20.504
- Well, I know you clown,

03:20.548 --> 03:22.506
but I can't help it
if she saw the vibe in us.

03:22.550 --> 03:24.726
- Oh, our vibe, huh?

03:24.769 --> 03:27.032
And you are embracing our vibe?

03:27.076 --> 03:28.338
- What's there not to embrace?

03:28.382 --> 03:32.081
I mean, love is love...is love.
[chuckles]

03:32.124 --> 03:34.779
Hey, look, we do us.

03:38.130 --> 03:40.916
- Attached at the hip
with a total corporate shill.

03:40.959 --> 03:42.570
In a dictionary
under "corporate shill,"

03:42.613 --> 03:44.963
it says, "See Veronica Fuentes'
LinkedIn page."

03:45.007 --> 03:46.443
- Mm, she is cagey, that one.

03:46.487 --> 03:48.576
However, her superpower
seems to be the ability

03:48.619 --> 03:49.925
to thoroughly
get under your skin.

03:49.968 --> 03:51.535
- That's why she does
what she does.

03:51.579 --> 03:53.450
She--she smiles, you know,
and she tells you

03:53.494 --> 03:55.539
what you wanna hear,
and she plays nice.

03:55.583 --> 03:58.107
Stroke, stroke, stab.
- And?

03:58.150 --> 03:59.717
- And I have five weeks left

03:59.761 --> 04:01.806
to leave a lasting impression
on this place.

04:01.850 --> 04:04.374
To stir up some good trouble,
you know?

04:04.418 --> 04:06.507
And despite my best effort,

04:06.550 --> 04:08.378
Veronica Fuentes
is gonna come in

04:08.422 --> 04:10.119
and undo everything
that I've fought for.

04:10.162 --> 04:12.600
- Funny enough, I, too, have
just a little over a month

04:12.643 --> 04:14.384
in which to affix
a lasting imprimatur

04:14.428 --> 04:15.733
on the oncology department.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.344
- It's fancier
than the way I said it.

04:17.387 --> 04:18.910
- I've put my heart and soul
into oncology.

04:18.954 --> 04:20.999
I'm gonna leave it
ship-shape in Bristol fashion.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.828
- Good. What?
- A well-oiled machine, dear.

04:23.872 --> 04:25.569
So while you're busy
stirring up good trouble,

04:25.613 --> 04:27.484
I will be dotting my Is
and crossing my Ts,

04:27.528 --> 04:29.704
updating patient files,
replacing old equipment,

04:29.747 --> 04:31.488
even sprucing up my office.

04:31.532 --> 04:32.881
By the time
I leave New Amsterdam,

04:32.924 --> 04:34.883
I'll have everything
in perfect order.

04:40.062 --> 04:41.890
- We're very different.

04:41.933 --> 04:45.937
- I need your help,
'cause I am going crazy.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.766
Leyla is working nights
this month, and we go days

04:48.810 --> 04:52.553
without seeing each other,
and it is making me insane.

04:52.596 --> 04:53.771
- No, you're missing
your girlfriend.

04:53.815 --> 04:54.946
That sounds perfectly normal.

04:54.990 --> 04:56.078
- No, not like this.

04:56.121 --> 04:58.080
I mean, this is like
a--like a need.

04:58.123 --> 05:03.215
Like--like a craving
for her smell and her touch.

05:03.259 --> 05:04.347
- Okay, let me ask you this.

05:04.391 --> 05:05.783
Have you lashed out at Leyla?

05:05.827 --> 05:07.959
Have you blamed her unfairly
for things?

05:08.003 --> 05:09.134
- No, no.

05:09.178 --> 05:11.093
- You abusing your power
at work at all?

05:11.136 --> 05:12.268
Adjusting the work schedule

05:12.312 --> 05:14.052
to make your life
a little easier?

05:16.011 --> 05:17.839
Okay, so that is
a slippery slope, my friend,

05:17.882 --> 05:19.971
one that you've
skied down before.

05:20.015 --> 05:21.669
- Oh, God.

05:21.712 --> 05:23.801
God, I'm making Leyla
my new drug, aren't I?

05:23.845 --> 05:25.629
- Well, I don't know.
I mean, I wouldn't

05:25.673 --> 05:27.196
slalom down that hill just yet.

05:27.239 --> 05:28.806
I mean, you're willingly
acknowledging your behavior.

05:28.850 --> 05:30.417
That's huge.
That's a big step, right?

05:30.460 --> 05:32.593
You've worked really hard
to be here.

05:32.636 --> 05:35.552
So I would say, uh, hash it out
with your sponsor,

05:35.596 --> 05:38.381
and focus on your triggers.

05:38.425 --> 05:39.991
- Yeah, thank you.
You're right.

05:40.035 --> 05:41.689
- Yeah, you got it.

05:41.732 --> 05:44.387
- Uh, and you know, if you ever
wanna get back in the saddle,

05:44.431 --> 05:46.476
you know, seeing patients...

05:46.520 --> 05:47.825
you still got it.

05:47.869 --> 05:49.827
- Ah.

05:49.871 --> 05:50.959
Cool.

05:51.002 --> 05:52.917
- Hi, Doc.
You wanted to see me?

05:52.961 --> 05:54.179
- Ah, Adena. Yes.

05:54.223 --> 05:55.616
Please, do come in.

05:56.834 --> 05:58.401
So you know how I'm trying

05:58.445 --> 05:59.968
not to leave any
unresolved department issues?

06:00.011 --> 06:02.884
- Sure, sounds like you.
- [chuckles] Yes.

06:02.927 --> 06:08.716
And I found a list of people
who had had mammograms

06:08.759 --> 06:12.720
who were identified
as having dense breast tissue,

06:12.763 --> 06:15.549
but who didn't follow up on
the letter that they received.

06:16.724 --> 06:18.378
I found your name on that list.

06:18.900 --> 06:20.118
- You mean that letter where

06:20.162 --> 06:21.816
they say you have dense
breast tissue,

06:21.859 --> 06:23.644
but we couldn't see everything?

06:23.687 --> 06:25.515
Yeah, I get it every year.

06:25.559 --> 06:28.083
- So why didn't you follow up?

06:28.126 --> 06:29.476
- Was I supposed to?

06:30.128 --> 06:32.479
- Okay, to rely solely
on mammograms

06:32.522 --> 06:34.176
when you have
dense breast tissue

06:34.219 --> 06:36.831
could place you at higher risk
for undetected breast cancer.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.181
Now, an ultrasound or an MRI

06:39.224 --> 06:42.271
is the best way to establish
a definitive baseline scan.

06:42.314 --> 06:43.925
- Well, when you put it
that way,

06:43.968 --> 06:46.536
it sounds
a bit more motivating.

06:46.580 --> 06:49.147
- And you've worked in oncology
for 15 years.

06:49.191 --> 06:51.149
I have a feeling
that every patient on that list

06:51.193 --> 06:53.543
needs to be having
this conversation.

06:53.587 --> 06:56.546
Now, where do we keep the files
with the letters like yours in?

06:56.590 --> 06:58.069
- Technically,
they're not patients,

06:58.113 --> 07:02.160
so we just kind of keep
their files in limbo land.

07:02.204 --> 07:09.124
♪

07:10.778 --> 07:12.214
- She's over there.

07:12.257 --> 07:13.476
Name's Carrie Logandorffer.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.347
- Has she vomited
any more bowel or blood?

07:15.391 --> 07:16.827
- Not since the ultrasound.

07:16.871 --> 07:18.350
I still have no idea
what's causing

07:18.394 --> 07:19.787
the shadow on her abdomen,
she hasn't passed anything.

07:19.830 --> 07:20.831
- Just breathe, Carrie.

07:20.875 --> 07:21.832
- This is Dr. Reynolds.

07:21.876 --> 07:23.094
He'll handle it from here.

07:23.138 --> 07:25.270
- Hey, Carrie,
and you must be her coach.

07:25.314 --> 07:26.489
- Jessa Wilkes.

07:26.533 --> 07:28.099
We're in town
for dance regionals.

07:28.143 --> 07:29.579
We were practicing,

07:29.623 --> 07:31.363
and then all of a sudden,
Carrie collapsed.

07:31.407 --> 07:32.626
Then she started vomiting.

07:32.669 --> 07:33.714
Scared us half to death.

07:33.757 --> 07:35.063
Her parents are on the way.

07:35.106 --> 07:36.412
- Okay, Carrie,
I'm gonna touch your stomach,

07:36.456 --> 07:38.196
if that's okay.

07:38.240 --> 07:41.199
Have you experienced any
other symptoms besides pain?

07:41.243 --> 07:43.506
- Oh--just kind of dizzy.

07:43.550 --> 07:45.116
- Okay, yeah.
We're concerned

07:45.160 --> 07:46.901
you might have some blockage
in your belly area.

07:46.944 --> 07:47.989
We're gonna
take a look at that.

07:48.032 --> 07:49.381
Okay? All right?

07:49.425 --> 07:50.861
I'll keep you posted
until her parents get here.

07:50.905 --> 07:52.472
- Okay, thank you very much.

07:52.515 --> 07:53.516
- Feel better, Carrie!
- Bye!

07:53.560 --> 07:54.778
- Stay strong, girl!

07:54.822 --> 07:56.780
- I'm still waiting
on your medical file,

07:56.824 --> 07:58.695
but do you know if you have

07:58.739 --> 08:01.132
sickle cell disease
or the trait?

08:02.482 --> 08:03.831
- Trait?

08:03.874 --> 08:05.746
I'm--I'm sorry. Sickle what?

08:05.789 --> 08:08.313
- Sickle cell, it's common
among African-Americans.

08:08.357 --> 08:10.620
- What? No, I'm not Black.

08:10.664 --> 08:14.450
[indistinct PA announcement]

08:14.494 --> 08:17.497
♪

08:17.540 --> 08:19.324
- Dr. Fuentes.

08:19.368 --> 08:20.761
Hey, I owe you an apology.

08:20.804 --> 08:22.066
I had no idea who you were

08:22.110 --> 08:23.938
when I had you bounced
out of the ED.

08:23.981 --> 08:25.505
- Oh, it's like being back
at CBGB's.

08:25.548 --> 08:26.984
- Indeed.
- [laughs]

08:27.028 --> 08:28.638
- So look, about this
little donation that we got--

08:28.682 --> 08:30.684
- Uh, you heard about that?
- Uh, yeah. Yeah.

08:30.727 --> 08:32.250
And if you haven't figured out
what to do with it yet--

08:32.294 --> 08:33.643
- I'm figuring that out
right now, actually.

08:33.687 --> 08:35.123
- Actually,
we're figuring that out.

08:35.166 --> 08:37.255
What you got?
- Yeah, but talk to me.

08:37.299 --> 08:38.996
- Okay, I honestly have
no idea who to look at.

08:39.040 --> 08:40.520
both: Me.

08:40.563 --> 08:44.001
- Anyway, what about an
elevated urgent care facility?

08:44.045 --> 08:46.743
Better equipped
with an ED resident rotation?

08:46.787 --> 08:48.092
- Ooh, I like
the sound of that.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.920
- Yeah, we will take it
under consideration.

08:49.964 --> 08:52.357
- But not before you consider
a geriatric drop-in center.

08:52.401 --> 08:55.230
Kaboom. Dr. Ignatius Frome.
We've met before.

08:55.273 --> 08:56.710
- Sorry, you heard
about that too?

08:56.753 --> 08:58.276
- Seniors are just
so often neglected.

08:58.320 --> 09:00.365
It causes higher rates
of depression, homelessness,

09:00.409 --> 09:02.542
and I thought
this might help stem the tide

09:02.585 --> 09:03.978
and foster connectedness,
you know?

09:04.021 --> 09:05.719
- Yeah, uh, Iggy.
- Yes. Oh, hi.

09:05.762 --> 09:08.678
Lame-duck, huh?
- No, no. Active duck.

09:08.722 --> 09:11.333
- Oh, Dr. Fuentes.
I'm Dr. Lyn Malvo.

09:11.376 --> 09:12.508
- I'm Dr. Agnes Kao.

09:12.552 --> 09:14.510
- Chair of obstetrics
and gynecology.

09:14.554 --> 09:15.685
Chair of neurology.
- Impressive.

09:15.729 --> 09:16.686
- The new boss
did her homework.

09:16.730 --> 09:18.079
- Old boss still here, gang.

09:18.122 --> 09:19.820
- I heard we picked up
a new satellite property--

09:19.863 --> 09:21.865
- Uh, yeah, the land
is actually already spoken for.

09:21.909 --> 09:23.606
- But I have a great idea.
- As do I, Dr. Fuentes.

09:23.650 --> 09:25.216
- Uh, still here, gang.

09:25.260 --> 09:27.871
- Good, because a new birthing
facility would be optimal.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.525
The lack of quality
prenatal care has severely

09:29.569 --> 09:31.788
affected birthing outcomes
in this area of the city.

09:31.832 --> 09:33.703
- And there's a lack
of neurologic care.

09:33.747 --> 09:35.400
The area is rife
with chronic illnesses

09:35.444 --> 09:36.619
that often expresses conditions

09:36.663 --> 09:38.055
like seizure and stroke,
and if I had

09:38.099 --> 09:39.883
neurological screening
and rehabilitation there,

09:39.927 --> 09:41.406
and we reduce
our hospital census.

09:41.450 --> 09:42.582
- Killer idea, Kao,

09:42.625 --> 09:43.583
right next to my
drop-in center, right?

09:43.626 --> 09:45.149
Plenty of room.

09:45.193 --> 09:48.022
- These are all wonderful,
wonderful ideas, I have to say.

09:48.065 --> 09:49.893
- Dr. Fuentes--
- Not you too.

09:49.937 --> 09:51.895
- Totally controversial,
but I think laser-tag

09:51.939 --> 09:53.854
would go gangbusters there.

09:53.897 --> 09:55.899
That and Dr. Reynolds
wanted me to suggest

09:55.943 --> 09:57.292
a elective surgery center

09:57.335 --> 09:58.641
in case, you know,
you didn't go for laser--

09:58.685 --> 10:00.904
- Guys!
Love all your ideas, really.

10:00.948 --> 10:03.167
I don't know when this became
Land-grab Tuesday,

10:03.211 --> 10:06.040
but the decision
for how this land will be used

10:06.083 --> 10:07.737
will be made
the New Amsterdam way,

10:07.781 --> 10:09.086
meaning it won't come from us.

10:09.130 --> 10:11.045
- No, it'll come
from the community.

10:11.088 --> 10:12.568
We'll reach out directly
to the people

10:12.612 --> 10:16.267
and we'll find out
what their greatest needs are.

10:16.311 --> 10:19.140
- Yeah.
That's what I was gonna say.

10:21.969 --> 10:22.360
.

10:22.404 --> 10:25.276
- While this land may be our
project, it is not our focus.

10:25.320 --> 10:27.757
We're here to talk
to the community

10:27.801 --> 10:30.064
about their needs
and their concerns,

10:30.107 --> 10:31.631
and we're here to listen.

10:31.674 --> 10:34.024
Think of it like an
intelligence-gathering mission.

10:34.068 --> 10:35.591
- Okay, well,
that being said,

10:35.635 --> 10:37.549
they definitely do not need
another Chicken O'Cluck.

10:37.593 --> 10:40.248
- Well, whatever decision
we do make, these people

10:40.291 --> 10:41.728
and whoever is still working
for New Amsterdam

10:41.771 --> 10:43.555
will have to live with it
for a very long time.

10:43.599 --> 10:45.122
So I think it's very important
that we--

10:45.166 --> 10:47.255
- Welcome to Desmond Park!

10:47.298 --> 10:49.605
- Hi.
- How can I help?

10:49.649 --> 10:51.781
- Oh, well, that's
sort of my line.

10:51.825 --> 10:53.087
- Friends call me Domino.

10:53.130 --> 10:54.610
Whether it's direction,
confection,

10:54.654 --> 10:56.656
connection,
I'm all about satisfaction.

10:56.699 --> 10:59.093
Yeah, consider me your plug,
amigo.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.398
- Oh, my gosh, that's so cold.

11:00.442 --> 11:01.791
- Domino, I'm Max,

11:01.835 --> 11:03.445
medical director
of New Amsterdam--not her.

11:03.488 --> 11:05.273
So you know this area
pretty well?

11:05.316 --> 11:06.491
- Yeah. Know it?

11:06.535 --> 11:07.884
I grew up here
my whole life, man.

11:07.928 --> 11:10.104
Anything you want I can get,
and if I can get it,

11:10.147 --> 11:11.758
you probably don't need it,
yeah?

11:11.801 --> 11:14.021
Anyway, seven bucks
for waters, each.

11:14.064 --> 11:16.458
[man singing in Spanish]

11:16.501 --> 11:17.764
- I mean, look at this place.

11:17.807 --> 11:20.331
The kids make do,
but they shouldn't have to.

11:20.375 --> 11:21.942
Build a playground
into whatever it is

11:21.985 --> 11:23.334
that you're building.

11:23.378 --> 11:25.597
- So safer spaces for kids
to be kids

11:25.641 --> 11:27.208
and for people
to actually gather.

11:27.251 --> 11:30.820
- Yeah, and maybe
a closer OBGYN clinic.

11:30.864 --> 11:32.561
It's hard to get the time off
to get to the good one.

11:32.604 --> 11:34.389
It's, like, 11 stops away.

11:34.432 --> 11:36.478
[lively music]

11:36.521 --> 11:37.784
- What we need
is a homeless shelter.

11:37.827 --> 11:40.221
My wife and I
founded this church.

11:40.264 --> 11:41.657
Fed and clothed
at least a fifth

11:41.701 --> 11:43.572
of the folk
in this neighborhood.

11:43.615 --> 11:44.747
- A fifth?

11:44.791 --> 11:46.444
That's a--that's
a lot of pressure.

11:46.488 --> 11:48.142
How are you and your wife
holding up?

11:48.185 --> 11:50.579
- [sighs]
My wife's passed.

11:51.406 --> 11:53.495
- I'm so sorry. That's hard.

11:53.538 --> 11:55.323
I--I can't even imagine
how it would feel

11:55.366 --> 11:56.846
to lose the most important
person in your life.

11:56.890 --> 11:59.806
The most valuable conduit
to your flock.

11:59.849 --> 12:01.721
That's--that's a lot.

12:02.547 --> 12:05.725
- What kind of a doctor
did you say you were?

12:05.768 --> 12:08.292
♪

12:08.336 --> 12:11.426
- [speaking Spanish]

12:14.385 --> 12:17.519
[coughing]

12:18.433 --> 12:21.566
- [speaking Spanish]

12:28.399 --> 12:31.359
[woman coughing]

12:31.402 --> 12:38.366
♪

12:38.409 --> 12:39.846
- It's like a broken record.

12:39.889 --> 12:42.196
That's the third
Chicken O'Cluck in five blocks.

12:42.239 --> 12:43.284
- I guess this area is known

12:43.327 --> 12:44.198
for its "round-the-cluck"
coverage.

12:44.241 --> 12:45.373
[both laugh]

12:45.416 --> 12:46.678
- You know,
you may have fooled

12:46.722 --> 12:48.637
some of our employees
with your faux charm,

12:48.680 --> 12:50.334
but don't forget,
I know exactly who you are.

12:50.378 --> 12:52.032
- Max, it's been ten years.

12:52.075 --> 12:53.947
Please give it a rest.

12:53.990 --> 12:55.862
- Free of charge for
the lovely medical director.

12:55.905 --> 12:58.255
- She's not--
- Oh, Domino, you spoil me.

12:58.299 --> 13:00.867
Thank you. Hi, fellas.
- Hi.

13:00.910 --> 13:02.738
- Uh, we just wanted to talk
to you guys

13:02.782 --> 13:05.306
about any ideas
you might have health-wise

13:05.349 --> 13:07.830
about what
the neighborhood needs.

13:07.874 --> 13:10.311
- Jobs.
Definitely better jobs.

13:10.354 --> 13:12.530
- Okay.
- A gym would be really nice.

13:12.574 --> 13:14.837
- A strip club.
[laughter]

13:14.881 --> 13:16.578
I mean, you guys asked.
- For your health?

13:16.621 --> 13:18.449
- Strictly for my health.
- Okay.

13:18.493 --> 13:19.973
- I'm gonna get another chair
for Dr. Max

13:20.016 --> 13:21.713
before he gets all up
in his feelings, all right?

13:21.757 --> 13:23.106
- Thank you.

13:23.150 --> 13:24.281
- Ooh.
- You okay?

13:24.325 --> 13:25.717
Your foot all right?

13:25.761 --> 13:27.415
- His diabetes is acting up.

13:27.458 --> 13:30.157
- Come on.
- Type one or two?

13:30.200 --> 13:31.593
- Two.

13:31.636 --> 13:33.160
It used to happen when I
forgot to take my pills,

13:33.203 --> 13:34.988
but I've been on it all year.

13:35.031 --> 13:37.381
- You gotta rest it,
and it'll be okay.

13:37.425 --> 13:39.340
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- Who's next?

13:39.383 --> 13:42.125
- [speaking Spanish]

13:42.169 --> 13:45.085
[light percussive music]

13:45.128 --> 13:48.740
♪

13:48.784 --> 13:52.179
- Helen, to what do I owe
this pleasure?

13:52.222 --> 13:53.963
- Dr. Ketner, hello.

13:54.007 --> 13:55.617
Do you have any idea
how many of our patients

13:55.660 --> 13:57.271
have kept up to date
with their mammograms,

13:57.314 --> 14:00.100
but still have no idea whether
they might have breast cancer?

14:00.143 --> 14:01.231
- Well, if I had to guess...

14:01.275 --> 14:03.059
- Yes, this many.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.669
These many people were sent

14:04.713 --> 14:06.628
a vague letter
from your department

14:06.671 --> 14:08.456
telling them that they
have dense breast tissue,

14:08.499 --> 14:09.892
but that their mammogram

14:09.936 --> 14:12.460
might not actually be
telling them the whole story.

14:12.503 --> 14:13.461
- Well, that's not good.

14:13.504 --> 14:15.028
- No, that's not good.

14:15.071 --> 14:16.899
That's why radiology
is gonna reach out

14:16.943 --> 14:19.119
to each and every one
of these people

14:19.162 --> 14:21.991
explaining exactly what dense
breast tissue actually means,

14:22.035 --> 14:23.123
and then bringing them in

14:23.166 --> 14:25.865
for ultrasounds or MRIs,
as indicated.

14:25.908 --> 14:27.649
- Nothing would
delight me more.

14:27.692 --> 14:29.346
Place will be humming 24/7.

14:29.390 --> 14:30.478
- Great.

14:30.521 --> 14:31.783
- We just need you to get

14:31.827 --> 14:34.482
new referrals for each of them.
- [laughs]

14:34.525 --> 14:36.527
- But it's still
just a breast screening.

14:36.571 --> 14:38.442
It's only more targeted.

14:38.486 --> 14:40.662
- And insurance considers it
a diagnostic exam

14:40.705 --> 14:42.664
and they require it.

14:42.707 --> 14:44.666
- Right, 'cause why
draw one straight line

14:44.709 --> 14:46.711
when four crooked ones will do?

14:46.755 --> 14:48.583
I will get this sorted,

14:48.626 --> 14:51.891
and you--you will
be hearing from me.

14:51.934 --> 14:58.854
♪

15:01.509 --> 15:04.512
[beeping]

15:04.555 --> 15:05.992
- Bilateral kidneys, normal.

15:06.035 --> 15:08.820
10 centimeters
and approximately 160 grams.

15:08.864 --> 15:10.126
- No explanation for the pain?

15:10.170 --> 15:11.301
- No. Let's move north.

15:11.345 --> 15:12.650
- Retractor.

15:12.694 --> 15:14.348
[tense music]

15:14.391 --> 15:16.654
- Gall bladder, liver,
all look normal.

15:16.698 --> 15:17.917
Retract laterally.

15:17.960 --> 15:19.005
♪

15:19.048 --> 15:20.832
Ooh.
- That doesn't look normal.

15:20.876 --> 15:22.269
- Mm.
Her stomach's distended.

15:22.312 --> 15:23.313
Scalpel.

15:23.357 --> 15:25.925
[beeping]

15:25.968 --> 15:32.061
♪

15:32.105 --> 15:34.542
Ah, pills.

15:34.585 --> 15:36.936
- Looks like the cause
of her pain.

15:38.589 --> 15:41.723
- A suicide attempt?

15:41.766 --> 15:43.420
- I don't wanna talk about it.

15:43.464 --> 15:44.552
- No, we are going
to talk about it.

15:44.595 --> 15:46.032
- Yelling at her
isn't helping, Holly.

15:46.075 --> 15:47.294
- Are you kidding me?

15:47.337 --> 15:48.773
Our kid just tried
to kill herself, Clark.

15:48.817 --> 15:51.254
- Okay, let's--let's take
a deep breath.

15:51.298 --> 15:52.864
I know this is a lot to digest,

15:52.908 --> 15:54.431
but I think it might be best

15:54.475 --> 15:56.390
to call in
a psychiatric evaluation.

15:56.433 --> 15:57.913
- No.

15:59.262 --> 16:00.960
I wasn't trying to kill myself.

16:01.003 --> 16:03.963
- Then why else would you take
a bunch of pills?

16:04.006 --> 16:05.051
- I don't know.

16:05.094 --> 16:07.009
- That's not
a real answer, honey.

16:07.053 --> 16:09.011
Not for this.

16:09.055 --> 16:10.795
- Carrie, look.

16:10.839 --> 16:12.754
Self-harm is serious.

16:12.797 --> 16:13.798
- I wasn't trying
to hurt myself.

16:13.842 --> 16:15.017
Why don't you believe me?

16:15.061 --> 16:17.019
- We want to.

16:17.063 --> 16:19.891
You're not just giving us
anything to go on.

16:30.902 --> 16:33.514
- They're skin lighteners.

16:33.557 --> 16:35.168
[solemn music]

16:35.211 --> 16:36.996
The pills.

16:37.039 --> 16:38.998
♪

16:39.041 --> 16:42.610
I wanted them to work faster,
so I just took a whole bunch.

16:42.653 --> 16:49.791
♪

17:02.934 --> 17:04.371
- There's a lot of
unchecked hypertension.

17:04.414 --> 17:06.460
- Rampant childhood obesity.
- Very few outlets

17:06.503 --> 17:08.114
offering emotional
support services.

17:08.157 --> 17:09.593
- Good jobs
was a running theme.

17:09.637 --> 17:11.030
- Heart disease everywhere.

17:11.073 --> 17:12.509
- What they really need
is a whole other hospital.

17:12.553 --> 17:14.685
- Well, the city's not gonna
foot the bill for that.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.035
- Then what's
our next best option?

17:16.078 --> 17:17.297
- Max?

17:17.340 --> 17:18.950
- Ooh!

17:18.994 --> 17:21.649
Ah, ah, I'm good.
- Okay, easy.

17:21.692 --> 17:23.042
- I'm good. I got it.
I got it.

17:23.085 --> 17:23.912
- No, no, no.

17:23.955 --> 17:26.610
Just have a seat.
You okay?

17:26.654 --> 17:27.698
Here.

17:27.742 --> 17:29.309
We're gonna take a look, okay?

17:29.352 --> 17:32.834
[dramatic music]

17:32.877 --> 17:35.097
- It's badly infected.
We can't leave him here.

17:35.141 --> 17:37.317
- Call transport now.
- I'm fine.

17:37.360 --> 17:39.449
- We're taking you
to New Amsterdam, okay?

17:39.493 --> 17:41.190
♪

17:49.155 --> 17:50.721
There's cheap fast food
on every corner,

17:50.765 --> 17:51.766
but if you want
a fresh head of lettuce,

17:51.809 --> 17:53.463
you gotta take two buses.

17:53.507 --> 17:54.856
You know, that's why this area

17:54.899 --> 17:56.684
is so full of chronic
medical conditions.

17:56.727 --> 17:58.860
There's no nutrition.
There's no food options.

17:58.903 --> 18:01.776
- Well, there's nothing we
can build to fix that, Max.

18:03.212 --> 18:04.735
- Sure, there is.

18:04.779 --> 18:05.867
We're gonna give
this neighborhood

18:05.910 --> 18:08.130
exactly what it needs.

18:08.174 --> 18:10.132
We're gonna build
a grocery store.

18:10.176 --> 18:12.439
♪

18:12.482 --> 18:14.093
- Welcome to New Amsterdam.

18:14.136 --> 18:16.573
♪

18:19.576 --> 18:19.794
.

18:19.837 --> 18:21.752
- Seriously, a grocery store?

18:21.796 --> 18:23.928
Look, I'm all for giving
unexpected objects

18:23.972 --> 18:25.234
to our patients.

18:25.278 --> 18:26.801
Next time a guy comes in
with a heart attack,

18:26.844 --> 18:28.237
we should give him
a little tinker toy.

18:28.281 --> 18:30.152
- Your snide mockery
of original ideas,

18:30.196 --> 18:31.675
I have so missed that.

18:31.719 --> 18:33.547
- Oh, please,
like you've changed.

18:33.590 --> 18:36.158
You're still the same
idealistic, noble dreamer--

18:36.202 --> 18:37.507
- Guilty as charged.
- Wasn't finished.

18:37.551 --> 18:39.205
- Oh.
- You know, your naivete

18:39.248 --> 18:40.989
was awfully cute
when you were in your 20s, Max,

18:41.032 --> 18:42.991
but now that you're
smart enough to know better--

18:43.034 --> 18:44.427
- Well, Desmond Park
was redlined

18:44.471 --> 18:46.386
by the government,
depressing the investment,

18:46.429 --> 18:49.650
making it impossible for
anyone there to own anything.

18:49.693 --> 18:52.435
You know who could afford it,
funnily enough?

18:52.479 --> 18:55.656
Fast food restaurants,
and now it's a fast food swamp.

18:55.699 --> 18:57.571
- Okay, I think
you're skipping the part

18:57.614 --> 19:00.095
where this healthy--
and when I say "healthy,"

19:00.139 --> 19:02.358
I also mean "expensive"--
grocery

19:02.402 --> 19:04.360
can stand to make
any money at all

19:04.404 --> 19:06.362
in an economically
depressed area.

19:06.406 --> 19:08.103
- Right.
Well, that's the best part.

19:08.147 --> 19:10.061
It won't have to
because it'll be nonprofit.

19:10.105 --> 19:12.063
- [laughs]

19:12.107 --> 19:14.501
Oh, just when I thought your
idea couldn't get any worse.

19:14.544 --> 19:16.198
- Here I was,
all these years later,

19:16.242 --> 19:17.286
hoping you'd changed.

19:17.330 --> 19:18.853
- Oh, that's not fair.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.071
My hair's totally different.

19:20.115 --> 19:21.551
- It's not a joke.

19:21.595 --> 19:23.336
It's an opportunity
to make a lasting difference

19:23.379 --> 19:24.554
in people's lives.

19:24.598 --> 19:25.990
You were there today.
You met them.

19:26.034 --> 19:27.383
What do you think they want?

19:27.427 --> 19:30.125
An overpriced care center
for after they get sick

19:30.169 --> 19:31.213
or for us to help them

19:31.257 --> 19:33.215
not get sick
in the first place?

19:33.259 --> 19:35.086
We're doing it.

19:35.130 --> 19:37.045
- No, we're not, Max.

19:37.088 --> 19:39.178
- Really? Watch me.

19:39.221 --> 19:42.485
♪

19:43.051 --> 19:44.400
- I need a full
debridement kit,

19:44.444 --> 19:46.663
general surgery, and an OR now.

19:46.707 --> 19:48.230
- My bike,
somebody's gotta watch it.

19:48.274 --> 19:50.624
It's all I have.
- Someone grab his bike.

19:50.667 --> 19:53.627
[tense music]

19:53.670 --> 20:00.547
♪

20:02.113 --> 20:04.420
- Ah! Ah!

20:04.464 --> 20:05.813
- I'm hitting bone.

20:05.856 --> 20:07.075
- Crap.

20:07.118 --> 20:10.296
♪

20:10.339 --> 20:13.429
- Okay, Domino, your foot
is infected really bad.

20:13.473 --> 20:15.039
- You're gonna fix it, though,
right?

20:15.083 --> 20:16.693
- I can't, my friend.

20:16.737 --> 20:18.217
Look, the surgeons
are gonna come,

20:18.260 --> 20:20.001
and they're gonna take you
to the OR,

20:20.044 --> 20:21.872
where, most likely,

20:21.916 --> 20:23.744
they're gonna have to amputate
your foot.

20:23.787 --> 20:24.962
- What? No, no.

20:25.006 --> 20:26.225
What are you talking about?
- I'm sorry.

20:26.268 --> 20:27.661
You are in safe hands, Domino.
- No.

20:27.704 --> 20:29.532
Hold on a second.
Dr. Bloom, hold on a second.

20:29.576 --> 20:32.187
Dr. Bloom, please don't
let them take my foot.

20:32.231 --> 20:35.321
Dr. Bloom, please!
Please, Dr. Bloom!

20:35.364 --> 20:36.409
♪

20:36.452 --> 20:38.802
Not my foot, Dr. Bloom!

20:38.846 --> 20:40.891
Please!

20:40.935 --> 20:43.329
- Nokic, go back to where
we picked up Domino

20:43.372 --> 20:44.634
and grab his bike.

20:44.678 --> 20:46.201
- What do you want me
to do with a bike?

20:46.245 --> 20:47.724
- You pick it up,
and you put it

20:47.768 --> 20:49.683
in your ambulance,
and you know what?

20:49.726 --> 20:51.859
It better be here
by the time he wakes up.

20:51.902 --> 20:53.295
♪

20:53.339 --> 20:56.342
Go, now!
Thank you.

21:03.914 --> 21:05.960
- But you have
such beautiful skin, Carrie.

21:06.003 --> 21:07.440
We've always told you that.

21:07.483 --> 21:09.659
- I'm still trying to wrap
my head around why, kiddo.

21:09.703 --> 21:13.750
- You being adopted means that
we chose you for who you are.

21:13.794 --> 21:15.274
Remember?

21:15.317 --> 21:17.972
- Just tell us where
you got those pills.

21:18.015 --> 21:19.495
- Probably on the internet.

21:21.367 --> 21:22.324
- [clears throat]

21:22.368 --> 21:24.370
Mr. and Mrs. Logandorffer,

21:24.413 --> 21:26.937
uh, I'm gonna need to run
a few more tests on Carrie.

21:26.981 --> 21:29.200
Can you leave the room
for a few minutes?

21:29.244 --> 21:30.724
Thanks.

21:38.166 --> 21:40.473
- Are the tests going to hurt?

21:40.516 --> 21:42.562
- Just another blood draw.

21:42.605 --> 21:45.347
But you looked like
you could use a break.

21:46.783 --> 21:50.700
- Yeah, we're all
kind of crazy,

21:50.744 --> 21:53.312
and this is...

21:53.355 --> 21:54.704
- It's a lot.

21:56.315 --> 21:59.448
You know, Carrie, based on
how you're dealing with race,

21:59.492 --> 22:01.189
I'm still going to order
a psych consult for you.

22:01.232 --> 22:03.539
- I know I'm mixed race,
Dr. Reynolds.

22:03.583 --> 22:07.587
My bio mom's white,
and my bio dad's Black.

22:08.239 --> 22:10.329
That's why I look the way I do.

22:11.765 --> 22:13.941
- And you're tired of the way
your skin looks?

22:16.639 --> 22:18.815
- Only when it causes
a problem.

22:18.859 --> 22:21.514
♪

22:21.557 --> 22:25.692
Like when people stare
at my family

22:25.735 --> 22:28.303
or at the dance tournament.

22:28.347 --> 22:31.393
- Did something happen there?

22:31.437 --> 22:32.742
- Why do you care?

22:34.222 --> 22:36.964
- Because you're my patient,

22:37.007 --> 22:38.269
and you don't know me,

22:38.313 --> 22:41.751
but sometimes it makes it
easier to say stuff.

22:41.795 --> 22:47.888
♪

22:47.931 --> 22:48.976
- We were changing,

22:49.019 --> 22:52.196
and I forgot my leggings
in the van.

22:52.240 --> 22:53.720
Coach Jessa let me go get them,

22:53.763 --> 22:56.026
but when I tried to get back
into the dressing room,

22:56.070 --> 22:58.028
this judge lady stopped me.

22:58.072 --> 23:00.291
I told her I was with
the Dancing Dells,

23:00.335 --> 23:04.383
but she said that there was
no way I could be with them.

23:04.426 --> 23:06.994
And she just wouldn't
let me in.

23:09.736 --> 23:11.781
Then, like, forever later,
Coach Jessa came out,

23:11.825 --> 23:15.002
and she was mad
that I took so long.

23:15.045 --> 23:17.874
- Well, did you explain
what happened?

23:17.918 --> 23:20.703
- Yeah, but she said

23:20.747 --> 23:24.141
that the lady
had just made a mistake.

23:24.185 --> 23:25.491
No big deal.

23:27.580 --> 23:29.059
- But it felt like one.

23:29.103 --> 23:33.150
♪

23:33.194 --> 23:34.717
- I just...

23:36.893 --> 23:41.071
I just wanna be like
everyone else in my family.

23:41.115 --> 23:44.466
♪

23:44.510 --> 23:47.426
[light percussive music]

23:47.469 --> 23:50.603
♪

23:50.646 --> 23:52.474
- Oh! No!
- No, no, no!

23:52.518 --> 23:54.737
- Okay.
All right, don't panic.

23:54.781 --> 23:56.304
This isn't bad as it looks.

23:56.347 --> 23:58.654
We'll just---we'll shove it
back inside the box, right?

23:58.698 --> 24:01.222
- They're supposed
to be alphabetical.

24:01.265 --> 24:03.442
- Oh, my God. What?

24:03.485 --> 24:05.835
Okay, yeah, this is horrendous.

24:05.879 --> 24:09.099
- I started thinking today
about my legacy,

24:09.143 --> 24:10.536
and now life has provided me

24:10.579 --> 24:11.667
with the perfect symbol for it.

24:11.711 --> 24:13.843
- Cautionary tale
for paper cuts?

24:13.887 --> 24:17.456
- A big mess that everyone else
has helped clean up.

24:17.499 --> 24:19.022
- Oh, please.
You are not messy.

24:19.066 --> 24:21.503
You're drawn to mess.

24:21.547 --> 24:22.983
You're dating Max, are you not?

24:23.026 --> 24:24.854
- [chuckles]

24:24.898 --> 24:26.987
You're right there.
- Yeah, I know.

24:27.030 --> 24:29.685
- But the ironic thing
is that's

24:29.729 --> 24:31.513
one of my favorite things
about him.

24:31.557 --> 24:32.688
- Oh.
- When something isn't working,

24:32.732 --> 24:34.429
he creates a mess
on purpose, right?

24:34.473 --> 24:36.083
To force people
to pay attention

24:36.126 --> 24:37.519
so that something gets done,

24:37.563 --> 24:39.129
and if some people
don't like it

24:39.173 --> 24:42.611
what he is "supposed" to do,
he doesn't care.

24:42.655 --> 24:44.787
It just rolls right off him.
How does he do that?

24:44.831 --> 24:46.093
- I mean, I suppose step one

24:46.136 --> 24:47.964
is being a tall, hot,
straight white guy.

24:48.008 --> 24:49.705
- [chuckles]
- Doesn't hurt.

24:49.749 --> 24:50.880
I just called him hot,
didn't I?

24:50.924 --> 24:51.925
I'm just--I'm just saying,
you know--

24:51.968 --> 24:53.883
[laughs]
You know what I'm saying?

24:53.927 --> 24:56.451
I'm saying we all know
that when women are disruptive,

24:56.495 --> 24:57.757
let alone women of color,

24:57.800 --> 24:59.367
they're labeled crazy
or difficult

24:59.410 --> 25:00.803
or a [whispers] bitch.

25:00.847 --> 25:03.980
And when Max does it,
he's a maverick with dimples.

25:04.938 --> 25:07.506
- Man, who couldn't I have been
if I wasn't petrified

25:07.549 --> 25:09.725
that the powers that be
wouldn't approve?

25:09.769 --> 25:11.597
- Well, if you want
that legacy,

25:11.640 --> 25:12.946
you may have to find out.

25:12.989 --> 25:15.470
♪

25:15.514 --> 25:17.254
- You should charge
by the hour.

25:17.298 --> 25:18.560
- Just saying.

25:18.604 --> 25:24.566
♪

25:24.610 --> 25:27.526
- It's time to make
a big, old messy mess.

25:27.569 --> 25:32.313
- Okay, then I'll just--I'll
take care of this, I guess.

25:32.356 --> 25:33.575
Yeah, no problem.

25:33.619 --> 25:34.707
- No.
- Just listen.

25:34.750 --> 25:36.012
- No.
- Are you gonna say

25:36.056 --> 25:37.536
anything other than--
- No.

25:37.579 --> 25:38.754
- Okay, I don't get
to explain?

25:38.798 --> 25:40.147
I don't get to make my case
to the board?

25:40.190 --> 25:41.409
You're about to say no again,
aren't you?

25:41.452 --> 25:42.758
- None of it, Max,

25:42.802 --> 25:44.325
because you don't make
the decisions anymore,

25:44.368 --> 25:47.067
not unless Veronica is behind
each and every one.

25:47.110 --> 25:49.548
And since I conspicuously
don't see her here

25:49.591 --> 25:51.462
joined at your hip as mandated,

25:51.506 --> 25:53.943
no new hires, no new programs,

25:53.987 --> 25:56.163
and just so
I'm perfectly clear,

25:56.206 --> 25:58.339
no grocery stores.

25:58.382 --> 26:02.778
♪

26:05.651 --> 26:06.042
.

26:06.086 --> 26:08.305
- Hi, you've reached
Dr. Leyla Shinwari.

26:08.349 --> 26:10.351
Please leave a message.

26:10.394 --> 26:11.395
[beep]

26:11.439 --> 26:12.658
- Hey, hey.

26:12.701 --> 26:15.356
I--I know you're sleeping.

26:15.399 --> 26:17.750
I saw last night's ED census.

26:17.793 --> 26:19.447
Brutal.

26:20.709 --> 26:24.713
I just called, uh...

26:24.757 --> 26:27.368
because I miss you.

26:27.411 --> 26:32.591
I know that's weird
and, um, very creepy,

26:32.634 --> 26:36.116
but just...

26:36.159 --> 26:37.291
I miss the smell of it.

26:37.334 --> 26:40.120
I don't know. It's...

26:40.163 --> 26:41.904
I don't know, like, you,
warm and rosy,

26:41.948 --> 26:45.473
fresh out of the shower.

26:45.516 --> 26:46.343
I can't--

26:46.387 --> 26:50.043
[phone beeps]
[sighs]

26:50.086 --> 26:52.523
I can't stand
being away from you.

26:52.567 --> 26:55.526
[soft music]

26:55.570 --> 27:02.490
♪

27:08.714 --> 27:10.629
- Oh, whoa.

27:10.672 --> 27:14.328
Unnecessary roughness
on the vending machine.

27:14.371 --> 27:15.677
The doctor declines
the penalty.

27:15.721 --> 27:17.810
What's up, man?
You having a bad day?

27:17.853 --> 27:18.941
- It's just a patient.

27:18.985 --> 27:21.204
It's not worth talking about.

27:24.512 --> 27:25.905
- Skin lighteners?
- Yeah, this kid

27:25.948 --> 27:28.647
is obviously struggling
with profound self-hatred.

27:28.690 --> 27:30.649
- Yeah, well, I mean,
before we label it,

27:30.692 --> 27:32.172
let's try and remember
she's a 13-year-old

27:32.215 --> 27:33.869
transracial adoptee, right?

27:33.913 --> 27:36.176
- One who almost died, Iggy,
'cause she's surrounded

27:36.219 --> 27:37.568
by no one who looks like her

27:37.612 --> 27:39.005
and has learned to hate
the color of her skin.

27:39.048 --> 27:40.702
How is this anything
other than that?

27:40.746 --> 27:43.792
- Yeah, but you're applying
your life experience

27:43.836 --> 27:45.315
and your identity to hers.

27:45.359 --> 27:46.621
- Yeah,
because I have no choice,

27:46.665 --> 27:48.710
and the way she looks,
neither will she, right?

27:48.754 --> 27:50.930
- Well, yeah, perhaps.
Absolutely.

27:50.973 --> 27:52.148
But that's her journey, right?

27:52.192 --> 27:55.195
Not a retread of yours.

27:55.238 --> 27:57.719
Identity formation
is about boundary testing.

27:57.763 --> 27:59.373
It's about struggle.

27:59.416 --> 28:00.722
And for her, it looked like
changing the color of her skin,

28:00.766 --> 28:02.811
which is extreme, yeah,
but it implies that

28:02.855 --> 28:06.032
she knows there's a difference,
which strangely is healthy.

28:06.075 --> 28:08.121
♪

28:08.164 --> 28:09.557
- Make it make sense.

28:09.600 --> 28:11.385
- Yeah, okay,
that was a little verbose.

28:11.428 --> 28:12.865
You said yourself
just over there

28:12.908 --> 28:14.214
that she is being raised

28:14.257 --> 28:15.737
bereft of people
who look similar to herself.

28:15.781 --> 28:16.869
- Right.
- Right?

28:16.912 --> 28:18.740
So she could have just
as easily denied

28:18.784 --> 28:20.220
that there was
any difference whatsoever

28:20.263 --> 28:22.048
and grown
into a cratering reality

28:22.091 --> 28:23.702
and just crushing her.

28:23.745 --> 28:26.052
You know, frankly,
these are complex issues

28:26.095 --> 28:27.618
for any teenager
to deal with, right?

28:27.662 --> 28:30.143
So they need to be around
people who are safe for them

28:30.186 --> 28:32.275
to be vulnerable with.

28:32.319 --> 28:34.887
- Like another person of color

28:34.930 --> 28:36.889
who can relate to the things
she's going through.

28:36.932 --> 28:38.586
- Yes, and you are her doctor.

28:38.629 --> 28:41.850
- And a Black man who has
lived through some things.

28:41.894 --> 28:43.547
I mean, someone's gotta
help her through the terrain.

28:43.591 --> 28:46.159
- I agree 100%, but not you.

28:46.202 --> 28:50.380
♪

28:50.424 --> 28:53.340
- My brother. Ah--

28:53.383 --> 28:55.777
Damn. Thank you

28:55.821 --> 28:57.605
- Yeah, and man, if you wanna,
you know, role-play it out

28:57.648 --> 28:59.912
or whatever,
talk about it more, I'm here.

28:59.955 --> 29:04.525
♪

29:04.568 --> 29:06.005
- Do I have breast cancer?

29:06.048 --> 29:06.962
Is this their way
of telling me?

29:07.006 --> 29:08.442
[speaking Spanish]

29:08.485 --> 29:10.705
[indistinct chatter]

29:10.749 --> 29:12.794
- Big plans!
I've seen "Beaches."

29:12.838 --> 29:14.187
- I'm just gonna--
excuse me, please.

29:14.230 --> 29:17.277
Sorry. Ladies. Ladies!

29:17.320 --> 29:20.497
- [whistles]
- Thank you.

29:20.541 --> 29:22.804
And thank you all
for your patience.

29:22.848 --> 29:24.371
I look forward to sitting down
with each

29:24.414 --> 29:25.633
and every one of you
and going through

29:25.676 --> 29:27.548
the breast screening options
in detail.

29:27.591 --> 29:30.029
- Please try to stay to one
side of the hallway, okay?

29:30.072 --> 29:32.118
Everyone to your right.
We can't block this area.

29:32.161 --> 29:33.293
Okay, ladies?

29:33.336 --> 29:36.078
- We need to talk. Now.

29:36.122 --> 29:38.951
[indistinct chatter]

29:38.994 --> 29:42.041
It's like the last few minutes
of a sample sale out there.

29:42.084 --> 29:43.651
Why would you
email them letters

29:43.694 --> 29:45.479
explicitly saying
that they could have cancer?

29:45.522 --> 29:46.741
- Because for years,
they've been receiving

29:46.785 --> 29:48.656
confusing letters,
so I told them the truth,

29:48.699 --> 29:50.049
albeit provocatively,
to get them in the door,

29:50.092 --> 29:51.180
and now they have
a real choice.

29:51.224 --> 29:53.487
- Being petrified
or very petrified?

29:53.530 --> 29:54.967
- Look, half of our patients
are flying blind

29:55.010 --> 29:56.490
on their breast health,
and we have to change that.

29:56.533 --> 29:58.666
- But we are obviously
not equipped to do that.

29:58.709 --> 30:01.582
You see this line?
That is just today.

30:01.625 --> 30:04.498
- Well, then we outsource.

30:04.541 --> 30:07.066
There's already a scan van
doing this kind of work.

30:07.109 --> 30:08.415
We help them scale up.

30:08.458 --> 30:10.634
We could send scan vans out
across the city.

30:10.678 --> 30:12.680
We could make it easy.
Patients walk up.

30:12.723 --> 30:13.942
They get their mammogram.
If they need

30:13.986 --> 30:15.683
the extra screening,
they get it on the spot.

30:15.726 --> 30:18.381
No waiting, no new referral,
and no extra charge.

30:18.425 --> 30:21.297
- It's a radical
and noble idea, Helen.

30:21.341 --> 30:22.559
Very Max of you.

30:22.603 --> 30:25.824
But these things
don't happen overnight.

30:25.867 --> 30:27.477
- Okay, well, maybe I can get
the ball rolling

30:27.521 --> 30:29.523
before I leave and then pray

30:29.566 --> 30:32.265
that my successor
keeps this a priority.

30:32.308 --> 30:39.446
♪

30:40.969 --> 30:42.710
How does Max do this?

30:45.626 --> 30:48.803
- You have to accept that you
may lose as often as you win.

30:51.284 --> 30:54.287
And from here on out, there's
gonna be a lot more losing.

30:54.330 --> 31:01.468
♪

31:10.216 --> 31:13.349
- [humming]

31:29.191 --> 31:30.453
- Max...

31:33.282 --> 31:34.718
Do you know why they hired me?

31:37.112 --> 31:40.376
'Cause you're building
too many grocery stores.

31:40.420 --> 31:42.422
Under your leadership,
New Amsterdam

31:42.465 --> 31:47.993
is running a deficit
of 21 million per quarter.

31:48.036 --> 31:50.038
That is $84 million a year.

31:50.082 --> 31:53.346
COVID dried up all your most
profitable revenue streams,

31:53.389 --> 31:55.435
and profit margins
are down overall.

31:55.478 --> 31:57.611
- Less profit equals more care.

31:57.654 --> 31:59.091
What else is the money for

31:59.134 --> 32:01.397
if not to spend it on
the people who don't have it?

32:02.572 --> 32:05.488
- Yet not all patients.

32:05.532 --> 32:08.622
In your efforts to end
systemic racism and bias,

32:08.665 --> 32:11.146
you have
unfortunately alienated

32:11.190 --> 32:12.974
so many of your white patients.

32:13.018 --> 32:15.629
- If amplifying other voices
is so threatening, then maybe--

32:15.672 --> 32:18.849
- Max, your lobby looks like
a progressive piñata

32:18.893 --> 32:20.982
just exploded.
- [chuckles]

32:21.026 --> 32:23.942
- There are so many
memorial plaques

32:23.985 --> 32:27.728
and so many apologetic
commemorative poems.

32:27.771 --> 32:29.295
I mean, you might as well
be getting a checkup

32:29.338 --> 32:30.818
at a Bernie Sanders rally.

32:30.861 --> 32:32.820
- And if money is all you care
about, then why don't you

32:32.863 --> 32:34.865
just turn New Amsterdam
into a private hospital

32:34.909 --> 32:39.522
and shut the doors on anyone
who can't pay enough to live?

32:40.871 --> 32:42.830
- I will take that
under consideration.

32:42.873 --> 32:44.614
- I think that's a good idea.

32:44.658 --> 32:47.095
- I have a lot of good ideas
for New Amsterdam,

32:47.139 --> 32:49.576
including what to do
with that land in Desmond Park.

32:49.619 --> 32:51.839
I am gonna sell it
to the highest bidder,

32:51.882 --> 32:55.669
and I am going to put
that money into our endowment.

32:55.712 --> 32:58.280
- Great, so not a single cent

32:58.324 --> 33:03.372
is gonna go to patients
or research or new facilities.

33:03.416 --> 33:04.895
- I already have an offer.

33:06.419 --> 33:07.724
- From who?

33:07.768 --> 33:10.814
- Unifell.
Huge corporation.

33:10.858 --> 33:12.338
You might know them
as the parent company

33:12.381 --> 33:15.558
of Chicken O'Cluck--
no, hear me out.

33:15.602 --> 33:17.125
They want to build a factory.

33:17.169 --> 33:19.736
What does that mean?
More jobs for the community.

33:19.780 --> 33:21.695
- Making the very food
that's killing them.

33:21.738 --> 33:23.784
There's no way
I'm signing off on that.

33:27.309 --> 33:30.530
- I don't need you to, Max.

33:30.573 --> 33:33.228
I'm gonna wait you out,

33:33.272 --> 33:36.579
and then I'm gonna undo
every bloated program,

33:36.623 --> 33:38.755
every underfunded clinic,

33:38.799 --> 33:42.890
and everything that you've
built on very shaky ground.

33:42.933 --> 33:44.457
♪

33:44.500 --> 33:46.589
It's coming down.

33:46.633 --> 33:51.333
♪

33:51.377 --> 33:54.597
- You know, all I've tried
to do is create a place

33:54.641 --> 33:55.859
where people can heal,

33:55.903 --> 33:58.514
people who have
nowhere else to go.

33:58.558 --> 34:00.125
A places where they can heal
physically,

34:00.168 --> 34:01.952
psychologically, emotionally,

34:01.996 --> 34:05.565
and I think...

34:05.608 --> 34:07.654
I think I've been
successful with that.

34:07.697 --> 34:10.048
♪

34:10.091 --> 34:12.572
- Oh, Max...

34:12.615 --> 34:15.749
I have never
in my entire career

34:15.792 --> 34:18.491
replaced a successful
medical director.

34:18.534 --> 34:24.627
♪

34:32.505 --> 34:32.722
.

34:32.766 --> 34:34.724
- She shouldn't suffer
any long-term effects

34:34.768 --> 34:36.074
based on our tests.

34:36.117 --> 34:37.640
- Oh, thank God.
- Thank you.

34:37.684 --> 34:40.991
- She's lucky.
I mean, kids are resilient.

34:41.035 --> 34:43.255
Please. Uh...

34:44.212 --> 34:48.521
But I would be remiss
if I didn't share my concerns

34:48.564 --> 34:52.568
about her identity struggles
that--that caused this.

34:52.612 --> 34:54.744
I mean, she's gonna need help
navigating through that,

34:54.788 --> 34:56.920
and as the only biracial child
in your family--

34:56.964 --> 34:58.139
- We're very aware
that we're raising

34:58.183 --> 35:00.098
a biracial child, Dr. Reynolds.

35:00.141 --> 35:01.838
- And we don't treat her
any differently

35:01.882 --> 35:03.884
than the rest of our children.

35:03.927 --> 35:06.278
- Yeah, but she is different.

35:06.321 --> 35:07.975
Very different
than her whole family,

35:08.018 --> 35:10.195
and the predominantly
white community

35:10.238 --> 35:11.544
you're raising her in--

35:11.587 --> 35:13.633
- You make that sound
like an indictment.

35:15.069 --> 35:18.681
- You might be feeling that,
but I'm just stating a fact.

35:18.725 --> 35:20.509
I mean, do you know what
happened at her tournament?

35:22.120 --> 35:23.599
A bigoted official
didn't believe

35:23.643 --> 35:26.080
Carrie was with her team
when she tried to rejoin them,

35:26.124 --> 35:27.908
and then her coach dismissed

35:27.951 --> 35:29.257
her experience
of the encounter.

35:29.301 --> 35:31.520
Called it all
an honest mistake.

35:31.564 --> 35:32.869
- [scoffs]

35:32.913 --> 35:34.436
It sounds like Coach Jessa

35:34.480 --> 35:36.395
was clumsily trying to handle
an awkward situation.

35:36.438 --> 35:37.961
- Right, but in the process,

35:38.005 --> 35:40.660
she racially gaslit
your daughter.

35:41.748 --> 35:44.707
[soft music]

35:44.751 --> 35:48.146
♪

35:48.189 --> 35:50.670
- She knows she can talk to us
about anything.

35:50.713 --> 35:52.454
There's nothing
we can't talk about.

35:52.498 --> 35:54.239
- Yeah, but you can't
put this on Carrie,

35:54.282 --> 35:55.283
Mrs. Logandorffer.

35:55.327 --> 35:57.590
I mean, she's a child.

35:57.633 --> 35:59.635
It's your job
to talk about race, right?

35:59.679 --> 36:01.202
I mean, how else
is she gonna get comfortable

36:01.246 --> 36:02.725
talking about it?

36:04.336 --> 36:06.642
- We just don't
wanna make a mistake.

36:06.686 --> 36:07.730
You say one wrong thing--

36:07.774 --> 36:09.428
- Everyone gets so angry.

36:09.471 --> 36:11.647
- Well, but you gotta be
willing to make those mistakes.

36:11.691 --> 36:13.301
I mean, we've all lived
long enough to know

36:13.345 --> 36:15.347
that there will be anger,

36:15.390 --> 36:20.178
but you need to get over
your own discomfort

36:20.221 --> 36:21.962
for the sake of your child.

36:22.005 --> 36:29.143
♪

36:38.283 --> 36:41.024
- Surgery went as well
as we could have hoped.

36:41.068 --> 36:42.112
Just below the knee.

36:42.156 --> 36:43.462
- Don't worry.
I got your bike

36:43.505 --> 36:45.420
and all your merch
down in the ED.

36:45.464 --> 36:48.031
Yo, one of my boys needs
a new pair of earbuds, so--

36:48.075 --> 36:50.033
- See if he needs
a new bike too.

36:50.077 --> 36:51.513
[solemn music]

36:51.557 --> 36:53.994
- Domino, I know
this is shocking,

36:54.037 --> 36:57.563
but you could have died
out there on the sidewalk.

36:57.606 --> 37:01.915
You're gonna recover,
and we're gonna help you.

37:01.958 --> 37:07.877
♪

37:07.921 --> 37:10.053
- Seeds?

37:10.097 --> 37:11.577
What am I supposed
to do with these?

37:11.620 --> 37:13.492
- Plant them.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.711
Your diabetes
got out of control

37:15.755 --> 37:19.019
because medication alone
can only do so much.

37:19.062 --> 37:20.977
You have to completely change
the way you're eating

37:21.021 --> 37:22.892
to have a fighting chance.

37:22.936 --> 37:24.546
Leafy greens, legumes,

37:24.590 --> 37:27.332
lean proteins--
healthy living.

37:27.375 --> 37:29.725
- What, I'm expected
to be Farmer John now?

37:29.769 --> 37:32.728
- Oh, I'm sorry, I thought
that I was talking to the guy

37:32.772 --> 37:36.254
who made 50 bucks off us
in five minutes flat.

37:36.297 --> 37:37.385
Bringing you an opportunity,

37:37.429 --> 37:38.865
but if that ain't you anymore--

37:38.908 --> 37:41.302
- All right, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Take it easy.

37:41.346 --> 37:43.870
No reason to put that kind
of energy out there.

37:43.913 --> 37:47.134
- Okay, well, that land
out in Desmond Park,

37:47.177 --> 37:48.657
they are gonna build
something on it.

37:48.701 --> 37:51.269
But honestly,
that's gonna take some time.

37:51.312 --> 37:53.183
- Yeah, with inspections,
planning,

37:53.227 --> 37:56.274
those permits gonna take longer
than a G train on Sunday night.

37:56.317 --> 37:57.840
- In the meantime,

37:57.884 --> 37:59.842
who's to say
what happens on that land?

37:59.886 --> 38:03.019
- Maybe somebody
plants some vegetables,

38:03.063 --> 38:04.760
sells the rest for a very--

38:04.804 --> 38:07.110
- Say no more.

38:07.154 --> 38:08.982
If it makes dollars,
it makes sense.

38:09.025 --> 38:14.509
♪

38:14.553 --> 38:16.294
Thank you.

38:17.860 --> 38:20.820
[warm music]

38:20.863 --> 38:27.827
♪

38:32.962 --> 38:35.356
- Oh, come on. I made plans.

38:35.400 --> 38:38.316
- Healthy living.

38:47.716 --> 38:49.414
[door opens]

38:49.457 --> 38:50.980
- Hey.
- Hey.

38:51.024 --> 38:52.547
- Sorry. Uh...

38:54.027 --> 38:55.507
I know you're not really doing
the whole therapy thing.

38:55.550 --> 38:56.899
- That's okay. Come on in.
- Yeah?

38:56.943 --> 38:58.727
